-- int_deduped_billing_events.sql
```sql
-- Deduplicate billing events, keeping latest event per subscription/month
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month
            ORDER BY event_id DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_billing_events') }}
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- int_subscription_with_plan.sql
```sql
-- Enrich subscriptions with plan tier, handling missing plans
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        s.subscription_id,
        s.user_id,
        s.plan_id,
        s.started_at,
        s.ended_at,
        s.status,
        COALESCE(p.tier, '(unknown)') AS tier
    FROM {{ ref('stg_subscriptions') }} s
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_plans') }} p
        ON p.plan_id = s.plan_id
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    user_id,
    plan_id,
    started_at,
    ended_at,
    status,
    tier
FROM source
```

-- fct_monthly_subscription_metrics.sql
```sql
-- Final fact table: monthly subscription metrics by tier and industry
WITH subscriptions_with_attrs AS (
    SELECT
        s.subscription_id,
        s.user_id,
        s.started_at,
        s.ended_at,
        s.status,
        s.tier,
        u.industry
    FROM {{ ref('int_subscription_with_plan') }} s
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_user_with_industry') }} u
        ON u.user_id = s.user_id
),
billing_with_month AS (
    SELECT
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount
    FROM {{ ref('int_deduped_billing_events') }}
),
monthly_metrics AS (
    SELECT
        DATE_TRUNC('month', b.event_month)::DATE AS month,
        s.tier,
        s.industry,
        COUNT(DISTINCT s.subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
        SUM(b.amount) AS total_mrr,
        COUNT(DISTINCT s.user_id) AS unique_users
    FROM subscriptions_with_attrs s
    LEFT JOIN billing_with_month b
        ON b.subscription_id = s.subscription_id
    WHERE s.status = 'active'
    GROUP BY
        DATE_TRUNC('month', b.event_month)::DATE,
        s.tier,
        s.industry
)
SELECT
    month,
    tier,
    industry,
    active_subscriptions,
    total_mrr,
    unique_users
FROM monthly_metrics
ORDER BY
    month DESC,
    tier ASC,
    industry ASC
